On May 3, 2018, Vice President Mike Pence delivered remarks in the Rose Garden to mark the National Day of Prayer at the White House. He emphasized the importance of prayer in American history and highlighted the support and belief in prayer among the American people. Pence mentioned that President Trump has taken action to protect religious freedom, and in these divided times, he encouraged Americans to pause and pray for the country. He concluded his remarks by sharing a Bible verse from Jeremiah 29:11 and expressing gratitude to those who joined in the National Day of Prayer.